section.section:
Notwithstanding the local government guidelines set forth in Article 95, § 22 of the Code, the guidelines required by paragraph (1)(ii) of this subsection shall:
state the types of investment in which moneys may be invested;
include guidance for the prudent investment of moneys based on claim experience, cash flow projections, income, liquidity, investment ratings, and risk;
authorize investments of moneys in equities, provided that investments do not exceed 30 percent of the surplus moneys;
provide that moneys not invested in equities shall be invested in accordance with Article 95, § 22 of the Code; and
prohibit borrowing of funds for the express purpose of investing those funds.

Subject to paragraph (2) of this subsection, a governmental self-insurance group may be formed by any combination of:
counties;
municipal corporations;
boards of education; and
community colleges.

text.section:
Subject to the approval of the Commission, a county that participates in a governmental self-insurance group may include in the coverage:
any unit created or funded by the county; and
regardless of funding:
the board of education of the county;
a community college in the county;
a regional community college in the county;
a housing agency of the county created under Division II of the Housing and Community Development Article;
a municipal corporation in the county;
a multicounty unit that operates in the county; or
a revenue authority in the county created by the State.
